  {panel}

At the moment we retrieve info for gadgets using a GET request.  GETs have a character limit.  If there are more options than the URL can handle, bad things can happen - JRA-18864 

If we use POSTs instead, we will not run into this issue.

h3. Issue Summary
The javascript snippet generated from the issue collector doesn't show the complete source in the url.
{code:html}
// Requires jQuery!
jQuery.ajax({
    url: "?collectorId=<COLLECTOR_ID>",
    type: "get",
    cache: true,
    dataType: "script"
});
{code}
Hence the issue collector doesn't appear in the page in which it's embedded.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create an issue collector of any type.
 # Verify the code in *Embed in Javascript* section.

h3. Expected Results
The url in the code should be absolute containing the full source:
{code}
https://<SITE_URL>/s/d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e-T/r5gghz/b/3/bc54840da492f9ca037209037ef0522a/_/download/batch/com.atlassian.jira.collector.plugin.jira-issue-collector-plugin:issuecollector/com.atlassian.jira.collector.plugin.jira-issue-collector-plugin:issuecollector.js?locale=en-GB&collectorId=<COLLECTOR_ID>
{code}

h3. Actual Results
The url is incomplete
{code}
 url: "?collectorId=<COLLECTOR_ID>"
{code}

h3. Workaround
Copy the *src* portion from the *Embed in HTML* section and use it in the url portion in the javascript code.
